narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: We do readings and then talk about them in class in groups of two or three. It's great for getting better at speaking. I'd definitely recommend it.
Yes, it is not too much work and if you have the right teacher, it's great.
I would recommend it so long as the student was willing to put in the time.
I would definitely recommend the course. It is interesting and enjoyable. The readings were varied and not too difficult.
Like Spanish?Want to improve at Spanish?Take it.
It's not a class that you are itching to take, but it's not that bad either. I heard it was an easy class, but it actually requires a lot of reaading and outside homework.
